---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="How It Works | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>How It Works</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard evaluates each outgoing AI request through a deterministic control boundary
      before the request proceeds to model execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <p class="section-label">Runtime sequence</p>
    <h2>Runtime Decision Sequence</h2>
    <section class="how-it-works-diagram">
      <img
        src="/how-it-works.png"
        alt="BeaconGuard request evaluation flow showing validation, deterministic decision, allow or deny enforcement, model execution, and decision evidence output"
        class="how-it-works-img"
        id="how-it-works-img"
        tabindex="0"
      />
      <button
        type="button"
        class="how-it-works-view-btn"
        id="how-it-works-view"
        aria-label="View full diagram in full-screen"
      >
        View Full Diagram
      </button>
    </section>
    <div
      id="how-it-works-lightbox"
      class="how-it-works-lightbox"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      <button
        type="button"
        class="how-it-works-lightbox-close"
        id="how-it-works-lightbox-close"
        aria-label="Close full diagram"
      >
        ×
      </button>
      <img
        src="/how-it-works.png"
        alt="BeaconGuard request evaluation flow showing validation, deterministic decision, allow or deny enforcement, model execution, and decision evidence output"
        class="how-it-works-modal-image"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Compatibility-Layer Path</h2>
    <p>
      Some non-native clients require a governed compatibility layer before BeaconGuard evaluation.
      That layer normalizes request shape and context into the structure BeaconGuard evaluates.
      It does not originate policy decisions.
      It does not weaken fail-closed behavior.
      BeaconGuard still performs the deterministic allow/deny decision and emits reviewable evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Enforcement Boundary</h2>
    <p>
      Applications do not need to embed AI governance rules in business logic.
      BeaconGuard places governance in a dedicated boundary where deterministic policy decisions
      remain consistent regardless of model behavior or prompt drift.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Deterministic Decision Path</h2>
    <p>
      For equivalent request state and policy snapshot, BeaconGuard returns equivalent
      decisions. This is the foundation for operational confidence, incident response,
      and reproducible reviews in financial workflows.
    </p>
    <p>
      Compatibility normalization occurs before BeaconGuard policy evaluation when needed.
      It is not a replacement for the deterministic decision path.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Input and Output Governance</h2>
    <p>
      Inputs require explicit context (actors, requested action, attributes, policy identity),
      so decisions are traceable. Outputs remain constrained to a minimal set:
      decision result, policy identity, and reasoning context.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Evidence at Runtime</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Evidence is emitted as structured records, designed for audit and investigation.</li>
      <li>Failure conditions are explicit rather than implicit.</li>
      <li>Decision provenance stays attached to policy identity and input context.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Reviewer Focus</h2>
    <p>
      A reviewer should confirm that the request path is normalized before evaluation, that policy evaluation
      produces deterministic allow/deny outcomes, that malformed or missing inputs fail closed, and that each
      execution decision writes reviewable evidence before model calls can occur.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Decision and Review Loop</h2>
    <p>
      A control outcome is produced before execution; allow moves to bounded model interaction, deny blocks by fail-closed policy, and each outcome is retained as decision evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Technical Deepening</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/architecture">Boundary and deterministic control components</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/enforcement-runtime">Enforcement runtime</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/threat-model">Threat model</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/deployment">Review deployment expectations</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/trust-assurance">Review Trust Center evidence surfaces</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .how-it-works-diagram {
      padding: 24px 0 28px;
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 600px;
      width: 100%;
      margin: 2rem auto 0;
    }

    .how-it-works-img {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 600px;
      display: block;
      margin: 0 auto;
      height: auto;
      cursor: zoom-in;
      outline: none;
      transition: box-shadow 120ms ease, transform 120ms ease;
    }

    .how-it-works-img:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
      box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(3, 8, 16, 0.45);
    }

    .how-it-works-view-btn {
      margin: 0.55rem auto 0;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      padding: 0.45rem 0.9rem;
      border-radius: 0.45rem;
      background: rgba(15, 24, 40, 0.7);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      max-width: 600px;
    }

    .how-it-works-view-btn:hover,
    .how-it-works-view-btn:focus-visible {
      color: var(--brand-primary);
      border-color: var(--brand-accent);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(115, 182, 255, 0.35);
    }

    .how-it-works-lightbox {
      position: fixed;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: 1100;
      background: rgba(2, 6, 13, 0.88);
      display: none;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }

    .how-it-works-lightbox.is-open {
      display: flex;
    }

    .how-it-works-lightbox img {
      max-width: 95vw;
      max-height: 90vh;
      width: auto;
      height: auto;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      background: #0a1220;
      box-shadow: 0 16px 42px rgba(2, 4, 10, 0.65);
    }

    .how-it-works-lightbox-close {
      position: absolute;
      right: 1rem;
      top: 1rem;
      width: 2.1rem;
      height: 2.1rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      background: rgba(15, 24, 40, 0.8);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .how-it-works-lightbox-close:hover,
    .how-it-works-lightbox-close:focus-visible {
      border-color: var(--brand-accent);
      color: var(--brand-primary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .how-it-works-diagram {
        padding: 18px 0 24px;
        margin: 1.2rem auto 0;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .how-it-works-img {
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .how-it-works-view-btn {
        max-width: 100%;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    const openDiagram = document.getElementById("how-it-works-view");
    const closeDiagram = document.getElementById("how-it-works-lightbox-close");
    const lightbox = document.getElementById("how-it-works-lightbox");

    const openLightbox = () => {
      lightbox.classList.add("is-open");
      lightbox.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "false");
    };

    const closeLightbox = () => {
      lightbox.classList.remove("is-open");
      lightbox.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
    };

    openDiagram?.addEventListener("click", openLightbox);
    closeDiagram?.addEventListener("click", closeLightbox);
    lightbox?.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
      if (event.target === lightbox) {
        closeLightbox();
      }
    });

    document?.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
      if (event.key === "Escape" && lightbox?.classList.contains("is-open")) {
        closeLightbox();
      }
    });
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
